## 2.2 Why Map is NOT Part of Collection?

| Reason | Explanation |
|--------|-------------|
| Different data model | Collection stores single objects; Map stores key-value pairs |
| No common behavior | Collection has `add(element)`; Map has `put(key, value)` — incompatible |
| Different iteration | Collection iterates elements; Map iterates keys, values, or entries |
| Design decision | Java designers kept them separate for clarity |

> 💡 **Interview Tip:** "Map doesn't extend Collection because it stores key-value pairs, not single elements. The interfaces are fundamentally different."

