## 6.2 ArrayDeque

ArrayDeque is a **resizable array** that works as both Queue and Stack. It is the **preferred** implementation.

```
ArrayDeque as Queue (FIFO):
  offerLast("A") → offerLast("B") → offerLast("C")

  [head] A ← B ← C [tail]
  pollFirst() → "A"

ArrayDeque as Stack (LIFO):
  push("A") → push("B") → push("C")

  [top] C → B → A
  pop() → "C"
```

### ArrayDeque Code Examples

```java
ArrayDeque<String> deque = new ArrayDeque<>();

// Queue operations (FIFO)
deque.offerLast("A");   // enqueue
deque.offerLast("B");
deque.offerLast("C");
deque.peekFirst();      // "A" — front
deque.pollFirst();      // "A" — dequeue

// Stack operations (LIFO)
deque.push("X");        // addFirst
deque.push("Y");
deque.peek();           // "Y" — top
deque.pop();            // "Y" — removeFirst

// Deque operations
deque.addFirst("Z");
deque.addLast("W");
deque.peekFirst();
deque.peekLast();
deque.pollFirst();
deque.pollLast();
```

### Why ArrayDeque over Stack?

| Feature | Stack | ArrayDeque |
|---------|-------|------------|
| Thread-safe | ✅ Yes (synchronized) | ❌ No |
| Performance | ❌ Slower | ✅ Faster (no lock) |
| Memory | ❌ More | ✅ Less |
| Legacy | ✅ Old | ✅ Modern |
| Null allowed | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| Recommended | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |

