### HashMap Interview Questions

> ❓ **Q: How does HashMap handle collisions?**
> ✅ **A:** Chaining — multiple entries in same bucket stored as LinkedList (Java 7) or Red-Black Tree when bucket size ≥ 8 (Java 8).

> ❓ **Q: What is the default capacity and load factor?**
> ✅ **A:** Capacity = 16, Load Factor = 0.75. Rehash when size > 16 × 0.75 = 12.

> ❓ **Q: Why do we override equals() and hashCode() together?**
> ✅ **A:** hashCode() finds the bucket. equals() finds the exact key within the bucket. If you override only one, the contract breaks.

> ❓ **Q: What happens if two keys have same hashCode?**
> ✅ **A:** They land in the same bucket (collision). equals() is used to distinguish them.

> ❓ **Q: Can HashMap have null key?**
> ✅ **A:** Yes, exactly one null key (stored at bucket index 0).

