## 7.2 LinkedHashMap

- Extends HashMap
- Maintains **insertion order** (default) or **access order** (LRU)
- Uses doubly linked list to maintain order

```java
// Insertion order (default)
LinkedHashMap<String, Integer> lhm = new LinkedHashMap<>();
lhm.put("banana", 2);
lhm.put("apple", 1);
lhm.put("cherry", 3);
// Iterates in insertion order: banana, apple, cherry

// Access order (LRU cache pattern)
LinkedHashMap<String, Integer> lru = new LinkedHashMap<>(16, 0.75f, true);
lru.put("a", 1);
lru.put("b", 2);
lru.put("c", 3);
lru.get("a");       // accessing "a" moves it to end
// Order is now: b, c, a (least recently used to most)

// LRU Cache implementation using LinkedHashMap:
class LRUCache extends LinkedHashMap<Integer, Integer> {
    int capacity;
    public LRUCache(int capacity) {
        super(capacity, 0.75f, true);
        this.capacity = capacity;
    }
    @Override
    protected boolean removeEldestEntry(Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> eldest) {
        return size() > capacity;  // remove oldest when full
    }
}
```

