## 7.5 ConcurrentHashMap

- Thread-safe alternative to HashMap
- Uses **segment locking** (Java 7) → **node-level locking** (Java 8)
- Much better performance than Hashtable

```
Java 7: 16 segments, each independently locked

[Seg 0][Seg 1][Seg 2]...[Seg 15]
  ↕        ↕                ↕
 lock     lock             lock

Multiple threads can operate on different segments simultaneously!

Java 8+: Lock only the specific bucket (node-level)
```

```java
ConcurrentHashMap<String, Integer> chm = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
chm.put("a", 1);        // thread-safe
chm.putIfAbsent("b", 2);

// null NOT allowed
// chm.put(null, 1);    // throws NullPointerException
```

